  "learn": {
    "heading": "Order doesn't change the answer",
    "intro": "<p>You can <strong>swap the order</strong> when you add or multiply and the answer stays the same. Adding <strong>0</strong> keeps a number the same, and multiplying by <strong>1</strong> keeps it the same too.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>4 + 6 = 6 + 4 = 10</strong> — the order flipped, the total didn't.",
      "<strong>3 × 5 = 5 × 3 = 15</strong>. Also <strong>8 + 0 = 8</strong> and <strong>9 × 1 = 9</strong>."
    ]
